ase in gravitational potential energy happens only for the mass of 3.0 kg. The increase in gravitational potential energyΔEp\Delta E_pΔEp​;ΔEp=mgh\Delta E_p = mghΔEp​=mghwherem=3.0m = 3.0m=3.0kg andh=0.9h = 0.9h=0.9mΔEp=(3.0)(9.81)(0.9)=26.5\Delta E_p = (3.0)(9.81)(0.9) = 26.5ΔEp​=(3.0)(9.81)(0.9)=26.5JThe energy is used for the increase in kinetic energy;ΔEK=W−ΔEp=90−26.5=63.5\Delta E_K = W - \Delta E_p = 90 - 26.5 = 63.5ΔEK​=W−ΔEp​=90−26.5=63.5JTherefore2.5v2=63.52.5v^2 = 63.52.5v2=63.5v2=25.4v^2 = 25.4v2=25.4v=5.0v=5.0v=5.0m s−1^{-1}−1\textrm{ }

